tiveRevision"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"packs":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/packs","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/packs"}},"revisions":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/revisions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/revisions"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"4"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90568"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"83"},{"type":"tags","id":"1150"},{"type":"tags","id":"1380"},{"type":"tags","id":"2097"},{"type":"tags","id":"3132"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7680"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"11290"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11869"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring a routine visit to the general practice, a 70-year-old man accompanied by his concerned wife seeks evaluation for memory loss. Despite the patient\u0027s claims of having a \u0022fine\u0022 memory, his wife expresses deep concerns about a significant decline in his memory over the past year, accompanied by increased withdrawal. Additionally, he has been experiencing fatigue, difficulty sleeping, and unsteadiness in walking. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient\u0027s wife reports episodes of confusion and agitation during the night, along with visual hallucinations. She mentions that her husband has become increasingly irritable and argumentative, displaying uncharacteristic behaviors such as hoarding items around the house. The patient himself appears disoriented and intermittently repeats questions during the consultation. Suddenly, during the interview, an unexpected noise startles the patient, causing his arm to twitch involuntarily.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pathophysiological descriptions is most in keeping with the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Small infarctions affecting multiple areas of the brain","Misfolded neuronal protein particles causing plaque formation and cell death","Insufficient activity of monoamine neurotransmitters","Inheritance of mutation leading to unstable expansion of CAG repeats","Imbalance between the production and resorption of cerebrospinal fluid"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESmall infarctions affecting multiple areas of the brain are more indicative of \u003Cstrong\u003Evascular dementia\u003C/strong\u003E, which typically presents with a stepwise decline in cognitive function rather than the rapid and progressive decline seen in this case of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is describes the pathophysiology of \u003Cstrong\u003ECreutzfeldt-Jakob disease\u003C/strong\u003E, the most likely diagnosis in a patient such as this, with rapidly progressive dementia, ataxia, myoclonus, and a prodrome of fatigue, sleeping difficulty and personality change.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInsufficient activity of monoamine neurotransmitters is a feature of conditions such as \u003Cstrong\u003Edepression\u003C/strong\u003E, but it does not account for the broad spectrum of symptoms, including ataxia, myoclonus, and visual hallucinations, observed in Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInheritance of a mutation leading to unstable expansion of CAG repeats is characteristic of \u003Cstrong\u003EHuntington disease\u003C/strong\u003E, a condition that typically presents with chorea, behavioral changes, and cognitive decline, but lacks the rapid progression and myoclonus seen in Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImbalance between the production and resorption of cerebrospinal fluid is characteristic of \u003Cstrong\u003Enormal pressure hydrocephalus\u003C/strong\u003E, which typically presents with a triad of symptoms including gait disturbances, urinary incontinence, and cognitive impairment, but does not encompass the wide range of symptoms observed in Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The clinical presentation of CJD can include cognitive decline, motor disturbances, visual hallucinations, irritability, and argumentative behavior, along with other features such as fatigue, difficulty sleeping, and personality changes."],"references":["Ninds.nih.gov. 2020.\u00a0Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease Fact Sheet | National Institute Of Neurological Disorders And Stroke. [online] Available at: \u003Chttps://www.ninds.nih.gov/disorders/patient-caregiver-education/fact-sheets/creutzfeldt-jakob-disease-fact-sheet\u003E [Accessed 10 September 2020].","1Appleby BS, ML C. Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease. UpToDate.\u00a0https://www.uptodate.com/contents/creutzfeldt-jakob-disease"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90568"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"4"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/explanationMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108156/relationships/explanationMedia"}}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90568","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90568"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-07T10:14:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-07T10:14:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90